# Dark Mode Rules (深色模式)

Every view MUST look correct in both light and dark mode. Never assume a color scheme.

## Color usage

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - semantic colors that adapt automatically
.foregroundStyle(.primary)
.foregroundStyle(.secondary)
Color(uiColor: .systemBackground)   // iOS
Color(nsColor: .windowBackgroundColor) // macOS

// ✅ GOOD - colorScheme-aware custom styling
@Environment(\.colorScheme) private var colorScheme
.fill(colorScheme == .dark ? Color.white.opacity(0.05) : Color.white)
.shadow(color: colorScheme == .dark ? .black.opacity(0.3) : .black.opacity(0.06), ...)

// ✅ GOOD - brand colors (acceptable as accent, not for backgrounds)
SCTheme.Colors.brandBlue  // OK for buttons, accents, gradients

// ❌ BAD - hardcoded colors that break in dark mode
.background(Color.white)        // blinding white in dark mode
.foregroundStyle(Color.black)   // invisible on dark background
Color(red: 0.9, green: 0.9, blue: 0.9)  // doesn't adapt
```

## Materials & Blur

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - materials adapt to colorScheme automatically
.background(.ultraThinMaterial)
.background(.regularMaterial)

// ✅ GOOD - GlassCard / adaptiveGlass() already handles this
GlassCard { content }
```

## Shadows

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - adapt shadow intensity to scheme
.shadow(
    color: colorScheme == .dark ? .black.opacity(0.3) : .black.opacity(0.06),
    radius: 8, y: 4
)

// ❌ BAD - fixed shadow (too strong in dark, invisible in light)
.shadow(color: .black.opacity(0.15), radius: 8)
```

## Text on colored backgrounds

```swift
// ✅ GOOD - white text on brand gradient (readable on both schemes)
.foregroundStyle(.white)  // OK when on accent-colored pill/badge

// ✅ GOOD - check contrast ratio
// Use .primary on backgrounds, .white only on vivid fills
```

## Checklist for new views

- [ ] No hardcoded `.white` / `.black` as background or text color (use semantic)
- [ ] `@Environment(\.colorScheme)` used if custom styling diverges per scheme
- [ ] Shadows adapt intensity to dark/light
- [ ] Tested visually in both appearances (Xcode → Debug → Color Scheme)
- [ ] Card/container uses `GlassCard`, `.ultraThinMaterial`, or colorScheme-branched fill
